Third-party model licenses
===========================

The MIT license above covers the Py-feat Live application code ONLY. It does
NOT cover the facial-expression detection models that the app downloads and
runs (via py-feat). Those pretrained models and their weights are licensed
separately by their respective authors, and several carry NON-COMMERCIAL or
research-only stipulations.

You are responsible for reviewing and complying with the license of each model
you use. See the py-feat documentation for the per-model licenses:
https://py-feat.org/  (Models reference)
